# ecom-image-agent

Local Streamlit MVP for tea e-commerce image generation. The app accepts one or more product images, runs a LangGraph workflow skeleton, and outputs placeholder listing images with Chinese copy rendered by Pillow.

## Current status
- Completed: project scaffold, config loading, typed domain schemas, local task storage, provider abstraction, Gemini provider skeletons, LangGraph node skeletons, Pillow text rendering, Streamlit UI, zip export, unit tests, workflow docs
- In progress: real Gemini prompt tuning, OCR-based quality checks, rembg-assisted preprocessing, richer tea-specific planning rules

## Install
```bash
python -m venv .venv
.venv\Scripts\activate
python -m pip install -U pip
python -m pip install -e .[dev]
```

## Start
```bash
python -m streamlit run streamlit_app.py
```

## Environment
Copy `.env.example` to `.env` and fill `ECOM_IMAGE_AGENT_GOOGLE_API_KEY` if you want to switch from mock providers to Gemini-backed providers.

## Directory overview
- `streamlit_app.py`: Streamlit entrypoint
- `src/domain/`: workflow contracts and schemas
- `src/providers/`: LLM and image provider abstraction and Gemini implementations
- `src/services/`: local storage, rendering, OCR, QC, and helper services
- `src/workflows/`: LangGraph state, graph builder, and node implementations
- `src/ui/`: Streamlit page and reusable UI components
- `outputs/tasks/`: persisted task inputs, artifacts, previews, exports
- `tests/unit/`: schema and text renderer tests
- `docs/workflow.md`: workflow notes for the current MVP

## Current limitations
- Tea is the only optimized category
- Image generation currently falls back to deterministic mock canvases by default
- OCR QA is scaffolded and can be expanded once PaddleOCR runtime is configured
- Chinese rendering quality depends on an available CJK font file under `assets/fonts/`

